French toast is good for a lazy, quick, and tasty Sunday breakfast. It is delicious with bacon and honey, and a warm or cold beverage of choice. Ingredients Preparation Step 1 Over low heat, butter the pan and let it get hot. Step 2 Using a bowl, beat together the eggs and milk then dip the bread in the mixture. Step 3 Fry the soaked bread on each side until it browns, for about 4 minutes. Transfer to a plate. Step 4 Fry the bacon and place it on top of the toast. Step 5 Drizzle with honey or maple syrup and enjoy with your beverage of choice.